main event: A witness observed a whitish light that was yellow, possibly the star Arcturus, for approximately 2 hours.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on 21 Sept 68 from 2250 to 0135Z., The object was seen in the eastern sky., The witness described the object as having a reddish casing., There was no sound associated with the object., The conclusion of the report suggested it was likely Arcturus.
